# Git Commit Messages

- Write every commit message entirely in English (subject and body). No Chinese or other languages.
- Never reveal agent, tool, or model identity in commit messages. Do not mention "Cursor", "AI", "agent", "assistant", "Claude", "GPT", "Copilot", or similar.
- Never add agent attribution trailers such as `Co-authored-by:` referencing an AI/tool, or "Generated with ..." lines.
- Keep messages factual and focused on the change and its intent.

```
# BAD
修复了导出 PPTX 的分页问题

# BAD
fix: pagination bug

🤖 Generated with Cursor
Co-authored-by: Cursor <ai@cursor.com>

# GOOD
fix: correct scripture pagination when a verse exceeds page capacity
```
